{ dbtimezone / sessiontimezone

 `dbtimezone` returns the value of the → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database[database's] timezone either in `+hh:mm` format or as name of a → development/date-time/time-zone, depending on the most recent modification
  of the time zone using `create database` or `alter database.`

  gh|Oracle-Patterns|/SQL/functions/date_related/dbtimezone.sql||

  gh|Oracle-Patterns|/SQL/functions/date_related/sessiontimezone.sql||

}
{ NEXT_DAY #ora-sql-next_day

code {
alter session set nls_language = 'english';
 
select
   next_day( date '2021-11-17', 'monday'   ) next_monday,
   next_day( date '2021-11-17', 'wednesday') next_wednesday
from
   dual;
code }
  
 
code {
alter session set nls_language = 'german';
 
select
   next_day( date '2021-11-17', 'montag'  ) next_monday,
   next_day( date '2021-11-17', 'mittwoch') next_wednesday
from
   dual;
code }

  See also `→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL/functions/date/add_months`

}
